rComments: The class had many papers but it was very well presented. Sometimes I didn't do readings because of their hardness, but Katz would explain it quite well in class to understand.

very helpful prof, i was not a philosophy student but he did not use too much philosophy because the class was open to everybody. he has a very through way of explaining the concepts. the class was VERY hard but he was usually there to help

few weeks into his third year class. i'm enjoying it already. It's my first time with him, and he has been great in teaching, responding to emails, and even office hours. He'll hang out extra time if it means he can help you. Very old fashioned though, still uses those paper projector things.

prof katz made some very boring topics sound very interesting and good. i took his class just to fulfill a major requirement but finished it loving the material. really helpful with essays and before tests as well.

Katz is a really smart professor, but he is also very accessible outside of class hours. His office hours are the most helpful I've had in all of my time at UTM. The tests get progressively tougher, but he makes sure you are ready for it. The exam was a cakewalk. Only issue could be he lets people ask a bit too many questions in class.
Professor Katz is a legend. A bloody legend. Take his class, you won't ever regret it.

Prof. Katz's lectures and office hours were some of the best that I had ever attended. He is a brilliant, and well experienced philosopher and individual - his anecdotes are always useful and insightful. He is not afraid to share his opinion on philosophical issues but he certainly doesn't push others to endorse the same point of view.

Very approachable if you ask him to clarify questions you have after class. Only downside is that he doesn't really answer your emails though, and shoots you down during lecture if you offer a differing opinion than his.

He's an amazing professor! The material was very formal and technical, but he did a great job at emphasizing the conceptual aspects. He was able to take some of the seemingly arcane elements of the material and make them thought-provoking.

Katz presents his materials in a very clear and organized manner. No matter how abstract the concept is, he can still explain in a way that students can understand. Going to his office hours help me understand the subject matter to a next level. I enjoyed his course a lot
Philosophy of religion. The material is thought provoking and the result is a well crafted course. There is a stress on logic, but what is philosophy without logic. Great course.

Loved first year philo with Weisberg because he made it SO easy to understand. Katz is ok..but if you challenge him and he doesn't know what to say he bypasses it/makes you look insignificant. Boring class...got nothing out of it really..i would not take that class again.
His class is really interesting. He is nice and helpful.

The course material is pretty difficult but he clearly explains the material making the information a lot easier.  His course made me think about logic outside of the class room, this is how interesting his class is. He is correct when he says one is never done with philosophy, even if you obtain a degree in it.  Thanks professor Katz :)
